latestPosts.caption:
Two years ago, I landed in Boston with two suitcases, a heart full of hope, and dreams too big to fit in either.🥹 I left behind everything I knew in Mumbai my home, my comfort zone, my people and stepped into a city where I had to start from scratch.

Today, I’m holding the degree I once only dreamed about. I graduated at 23, just like I promised myself I would. It still doesn’t feel real. I close my eyes and I’m back to being 16-year-old Lisha, staring at the ceiling late at night, imagining this life. She would be so proud right now.
And honestly… I don’t even recognize the girl I used to be. In the best way possible.
Boston has changed me completely.
There are things I do now, decisions I make, strength I carry… that the me from 3–4 years ago wouldn’t have imagined.
The girl who used to second-guess everything now walks with confidence.
I’ve grown into someone who chooses herself, who shows up even when it’s hard and does it all with grace. 💗

This journey was anything but easy.
I’ve cried over code that wouldn’t run.
I’ve pulled all-nighters trying to finish assignments.
I’ve questioned myself more times than I can count.
But I never stopped showing up for my dreams.

To my parents thank you for believing in me when I didn’t.
To my friends  thank you for being my home away from home.
To every person who encouraged me, cheered me on, or simply asked how I was doing you were part of this.🥹♥️♥️

This degree isn’t just an achievement. It’s a reminder that I’m capable of hard things, of brave choices, of chasing what I want even when it’s scary.

So here’s to the girl who took a leap of faith.
And to the woman she’s becoming.
Boston you will always hold a special place in my heart🥹💋
